visa_types.overview:
Overview

- Based on the Inter-ministerial Ordinance No. 12/2018 and specific instructions from the Brazilian Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
- This type of visa may be granted to the foreigner:
- I - spouse or partner, without any discrimination, in accordance with Brazilian legal provisions;
- II - child of a Brazilian or of an immigrant benefiting from a residence permit;
- III - stepchild of a Brazilian or of an immigrant benefiting from a residence permit, provided they are under eighteen years of age, or up to twenty-four years of age, if proven to be a student, or of any age if economic dependence on the inviter is proven;
- IV - who has a Brazilian child;
- V - Who has an immigrant child benefiting from a residence permit;
- VI - ascendant up to the second degree of a Brazilian or of an immigrant benefiting from a residence permit;
- VII - descendant up to the second degree of a Brazilian or of an immigrant benefiting from a residence permit;
- VIII - sibling of a Brazilian or of an immigrant benefiting from a residence permit, provided they are under eighteen years of age, or up to twenty-four years of age, if proven to be a student, or of any age if economic dependence on the inviter is proven; or
- IX - who has a Brazilian under their guardianship, curatorship, or custody.
- Documents required for siblings
- - For siblings over 18 years old, with no age limit: proof of economic dependence on the inviter;
- - Or, for siblings who are students, over 18 years old and up to 24 years old: proof of studies.
- Important: in accordance with the current legislation, the visa cannot be granted if the marriage was celebrated by power of attorney.
Length & extension of stay
Validity period: up to 1 year.
Limit / expiry date until which the first entry in Brazil must take place – counted from the date of issue of the visa.
Residence period: indefinite.
Determined at the moment of residence registration with the Federal Police – indicates the effective period during which the foreigner will be allowed to reside in Brazil.
Please note: if applying as the spouse of a foreign national who is the beneficiary of a residence permit in Brazil for a definite period of time, both will be granted the same residence period.
